**Full §391(a) context (verbatim, for completeness)**:  
**(a)** The Secretary of State shall charge and collect for:  
**(1)** Filing certificate of incorporation, $89, and if the certificate is in excess of 15 pages, $9 for each additional page;  
**(2)** Filing certificate of amendment of certificate of incorporation or certificate of merger or consolidation, $194, and if the certificate is in excess of 15 pages, $9 for each additional page;  
**(3)** Filing certificate of cancellation, $106, and if the certificate is in excess of 15 pages, $9 for each additional page;  
**(4)** Filing an agreement of merger or consolidation, $200, and if the agreement is in excess of 15 pages, $9 for each additional page;  
**(5)** Filing a certificate of ownership and merger, $200, and if the certificate is in excess of 15 pages, $9 for each additional page;  
**(6)** Filing a certificate of conversion of corporation, $200, and if the certificate is in excess of 15 pages, $9 for each additional page;  
**(7)** Filing a certificate of correction, $106, and if the certificate is in excess of 15 pages, $9 for each additional page;  
**(8)** Providing a certified copy of any paper on file, $50 for the first page and $9 for each succeeding page;  
**(9)** Issuing certificates of incorporation, $50;  
**(10)** Issuing certificates of good standing of foreign corporations, $50;  
**(11)** Any other service, $9 per page and such additional fees as are provided for in this chapter.

